You could do this in XAML using a [`MultiBinding`][1] and a [converter][2]. A multi binding allows you to bind multiple values and convert it to a single value for the target property. In your case, you would bind the three enabled state properties and and do a boolean AND as conversion.

The following multi-value converter returns `true`, if all passed values are `true`, otherwise `false`.

```
public class BooleanAndConverter : IMultiValueConverter
{
   public object Convert(object[] values, Type targetType, object parameter, CultureInfo culture)
   {
      return values.Cast&lt;bool&gt;().All(value =&gt; value);
   }

   public object[] ConvertBack(object value, Type[] targetTypes, object parameter, CultureInfo culture)
   {
      throw new InvalidOperationException();
   }
}
```

